<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15874">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Skating.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15875">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15875 mb-requirement-id-15876">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards associated with
        skating and what you should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate,
        and respond to these hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/skateboard-safety/"
          target="_blank"
          >Skateboard Safety (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15875 mb-requirement-id-15877">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while skating, including hypothermia, frostbite, lacerations,
        abrasions, fractures, sprains and strains, concussions, blisters,
        heat-related reactions, and shock. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.icliniq.com/articles/first-aid-and-emergencies/skating-injuries"
          target="_blank"
          >Skating Injuries - Types and Prevention (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15878">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Working under the supervision of an experienced adult, do ONE of the
      following options.
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15878 mb-requirement-id-15879">
        <strong>Option A—Ice Skating.</strong> Do ALL of the following: <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-53axkfHUHk" target="_blank"
          >How to Play Figure Skating (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8uDfC7sZ7ag" target="_blank"
          >How to Ice Skate (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15880">
        (1) Explain the general safety and courtesy guidelines for ice skating.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15882">
        (2) Discuss preparations that must be taken when skating outdoors on
        natural ice. Explain how to make an ice rescue. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KmYeulVH8IE" target="_blank"
          >How To Know if Ice Is Safe To Walk On (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/Education/OutdoorSkills/IceSafety"
          target="_blank"
          >Ice Safety (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BWLvW-d5jBY" target="_blank"
          >Test Ice Thickness (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yVXJQq41tTA" target="_blank"
          >How to Save Someone Who Falls Through Ice (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15883">
        (3) Discuss the parts and functions of the different types of ice
        skates. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/H6hUVU57Wpk" target="_blank"
          >Figure Skates vs. Hockey Skates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15884">
        (4) Describe the proper way to carry ice skates at the rink and for
        travel.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15885">
        (5) Describe how to store ice skates for long periods of time, such as
        seasonal storage. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/xCibThdzynI" target="_blank"
          >How Do I Store My Skates Correctly? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.skatepro.ca/en/a65.htm" target="_blank"
          >Care for Your Ice Skates (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15886">
        (6) Skate forward at least 40 feet and come to a complete stop. Use
        either a two-foot snowplow stop or a one-foot snowplow stop. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rhQY1_bTjVs" target="_blank"
          >Snowplow Stop (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15887">
        (7) After skating forward, glide forward on two feet, then on one foot,
        first right and then left. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-7QqRz2EZAM" target="_blank"
          >Forward Stroking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15888">
        (8) Starting from a T position, stroke forward around the test area,
        avoiding the use of toe picks if wearing figure skates. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-7QqRz2EZAM&amp;t=516" target="_blank"
          >Forward From a T Position (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15889">
        (9) Glide backward on two feet for at least two times the skater's
        height. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/dZsfWfYxqzw" target="_blank"
          >Skate Backward (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15890">
        (10) Skate backward for at least 20 feet on two skates.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15891">
        (11) After gaining forward speed, glide forward on two feet, making a
        turn of 180 degrees around a cone, first to the right and then to the
        left. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Lm1PXq9iFog" target="_blank"
          >Turns Around a Cone (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15892">
        (12) Perform forward crossovers in a figure-eight pattern. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/krBVgF52z8M" target="_blank"
          >How To Do Back Crossovers in a Figure 8 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15893">
        (13) Explain to your counselor the safety considerations for
        participating in an ice-skating race. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://healthcare.utah.edu/healthfeed/2022/02/how-speed-skaters-stay-safe-ice"
          target="_blank"
          >How Speed Skaters Stay Safe on the Ice (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://kidshealth.org/en/parents/safety-ice-skating.html"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Tips: Ice Skating (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15879 mb-requirement-id-15894">
        (14) Perform a hockey stop. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nIfU38nAYYk" target="_blank"
          >Perform a Hockey Stop (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15878 mb-requirement-id-15895">
        <strong>Option B—Roller Skating.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15896">
        (1) Explain the general safety rules and etiquette guidelines for roller
        skating. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/eXzKkXQCY_Q" target="_blank"
          >Getting Started with Roller Skating (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15897">
        (2) Discuss the parts and functions of a roller skate and their
        functions.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15898">
        (3) Describe five essential steps to good roller skate care.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15899">
        (4) Skate forward with smooth, linked strokes on two feet for at least
        100 feet in both directions around the rink and demonstrate proper
        techniques for stopping. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/znYKw5GQZVA" target="_blank"
          >Skating Forward (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15900">
        (5) Skate forward and glide at least 15 feet on one skate, then on the
        other skate.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15901">
        (6) Perform a forward crossover. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/VrgT9TPLANY" target="_blank"
          >Skating Crossovers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15902">
        (7) Skate backward for at least 40 feet on two skates, then for at least
        15 feet on one skate. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c7MLviMbw6A" target="_blank"
          >Roller Skating Backwards (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15903">
        (8) Skate forward in a slalom pattern for at least 40 feet on two
        skates, then for at least 20 feet on one skate.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15904">
        (9) Skate backward in a slalom pattern for at least 15 feet on two
        skates.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15905">
        (10) Shuttle skate once around the rink, bending twice along the way,
        without stopping.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15906">
        (11) Perform a series of two consecutive spins on skates, OR hop, skip,
        and jump on skates for at least 10 feet. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/d6Z91xZXNxE" target="_blank"
          >Roller Skating Two-Foot Spins (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15907">
        (12) Perform a stepover.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15895 mb-requirement-id-15908">
        (13) While skating, dribble a basketball at least 40 feet, then back to
        your starting position, OR push a hockey ball with a stick at least 40
        feet, then back to your starting position.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15878 mb-requirement-id-15909">
        <strong>Option C—In-Line Skating. </strong>Do ALL of the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15910">
        (1) Explain the general safety rules and courtesy guidelines for in-line
        skating.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15911">
        (2) Describe the parts of an in-line skate and their functions. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/dKYpuWcZ_Ak" target="_blank"
          >Types and Parts of Inline Skates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15912">
        (3) Describe the required and recommended safety equipment for in-line
        skating. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/z10SQgx_kRA" target="_blank"
          >Safety Gear for In-Line Skating (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GF4fs9-zMq8" target="_blank"
          >Putting on Your Protective Gear (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15913">
        (4) Explain four essential steps to good in-line skate care. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/67xp-AyQb3g" target="_blank"
          >Maintaining and Caring for Your In-Line Skates (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Jcery4HP7_s" target="_blank"
          >Cleaning Your In-Line Skates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15914">
        (5) Skate forward with smooth, linked strokes on two feet for at least
        100 feet. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fg1eMFnl61U" target="_blank"
          >Skating Forward (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15915">
        (6) Skate forward and glide at least 15 feet on one skate, then on the
        other skate. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iwtS9vr4r-Y" target="_blank"
          >Gliding on One Skate (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15916">
        (7) Stop on command on flat pavement using the heel brake. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/phN9uBIXkAw" target="_blank"
          >Braking with In-Line Skates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15917">
        (8) Perform a forward crossover. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RMIRnNr-PeQ" target="_blank"
          >How to Turn on In-Line Skates (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2-ULGoMvk24" target="_blank"
          >5 Steps to the Perfect Crossover (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15918">
        (9) Perform a series of forward, linked swizzles for at least 40 feet.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TbNlbqClkGQ" target="_blank"
          >Forward Swizzles (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15919">
        (10) Skate backward for at least 40 feet in a series of linked, backward
        swizzles. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/t3dO_3vh0Ig" target="_blank"
          >Backward Swizzles (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15920">
        (11) From a strong pace, perform a lunge turn around an object
        predetermined by your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/__N7lV59GMI" target="_blank"
          >Maneuvering Around Objects (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15921">
        (12) Perform a mohawk. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ytPUoplawVU" target="_blank"
          >Perform a Mohawk (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15922">
        (13) Perform a series of at least four one-footed downhill slaloms on
        pavement with a gentle slope. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mzA573nx7W8" target="_blank"
          >One-Footed Slalom (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15923">
        (14) Describe how to pass a pedestrian or another skater from behind.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15924">
        (15) Describe at least three ways to avoid an unforeseen obstacle while
        skating. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NP5w-A5aRSc" target="_blank"
          >In-Line Skating Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15909 mb-requirement-id-15925">
        (16) Describe two ways to get on and off a curb, and demonstrate at
        least one of these methods. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3hq3sID5emE" target="_blank"
          >Maneuvering Curbs (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15878 mb-requirement-id-15926">
        <strong>Option D—Skateboarding.</strong> Do ALL of the following:
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2MEZdB-qooU" target="_blank"
          >Jamboree - The Park (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15927">
        (1) Explain the history and evolution of skateboarding. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/m4AQtoDBC00" target="_blank"
          >How Has Skateboarding Changed Over the Years (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/f9JWlMZa0GE" target="_blank"
          >The Wild History of Skateboarding (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/w1mm3zDNyNI" target="_blank"
          >The Evolution of Skateboard Tricks! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15928">
        (2) Describe the benefits of skateboarding (physical fitness, balance,
        coordination, perseverance, and creativity) <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/VAh62ff8rys" target="_blank"
          >Benefits of Skateboarding (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6bu_9sI7QTI" target="_blank"
          >Physics of Skateboarding (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15929">
        (3) Explain the safety rules and courtesy guidelines for skateboarding,
        including right-of-way and communication signals and warnings. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Yw9bBDZ2kUo" target="_blank"
          >Skate Park Safety Rules (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zTVb4bmoiw0" target="_blank"
          >How to Ride Skateparks for Beginners (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/qrq6KlaIe8Y?si=4ljJ-qZ2IAeG-tPe"
          target="_blank"
          >Skatepark Terrain (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/903371803" target="_blank"
          >How to Ride Safely on a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15930">
        (4) Explain the protective gear needed to skate safely, including
        helmet, knee pads, elbow pads, and wrist guards, and show how to wear
        them correctly. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/skateboard-safety/"
          target="_blank"
          >Skateboarding Safety (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15931">
        (5) Describe the two main styles of skateboarding (street and vert), and
        describe common skatepark features (ramps, manual pad, rails, spine,
        etc.).
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15932">
        (6) Explain skateboard anatomy (deck, trucks, wheels, hardware, etc.).
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305105" target="_blank"
          >How to Select a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15933">
        (7) Build a board by assembling all pieces (deck, wheels, trucks,
        hardware, and grip tape) in the proper order. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/A6E403WMOXk" target="_blank"
          >How to Assemble a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15934">
        (8) Explain skateboard maintenance (cleaning, adjusting bolts, and
        replacing parts). <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.skatexs.com/blogs/news/9432593-skateboard-maintenance-for-beginners"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Maintain Your Skateboard (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15935">
        (9) Explain the difference between regular and goofy stance, and
        demonstrate your preferred stance. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fdSzhc7HXJ0" target="_blank"
          >Goofy vs. Regular Stance (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15936">
        (10) Demonstrate how to push, cruise, and carve on flat ground. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305608" target="_blank"
          >How to Push on a Skateboard (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305658" target="_blank"
          >How to Turn on a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15937">
        (11) Show at least two braking and stopping techniques. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/gLikGjxWCUQ?si=-VfkhrC8oTh1LEvf"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Stop a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15938">
        (12) Do a basic ollie and at least one variation. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305845" target="_blank"
          >How to Ollie on Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15939">
        (13) Show how to drop-in from coping.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15926 mb-requirement-id-15940">
        (14) Demonstrate THREE skateboarding tricks from the following types:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15940 mb-requirement-id-15941">
        (a) Flat ground tricks <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-LwtQJFqNOA" target="_blank"
          >Flatland Tricks (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305720" target="_blank"
          >How to Manual on Skateboard (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305789" target="_blank"
          >How to Throwdown on Skateboard (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/901305968" target="_blank"
          >How to 180 on a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15940 mb-requirement-id-15942">
        (b) Flip and shove-it tricks <br /><i>Resources:</i>
